## Header menuItems API (Three-Tier Display)

`fimbyPageHeader` accepts `menu-items` array, emits `menuaction`. Each item declares `display`:

- **`inline`** — Always visible action button (rounded rectangle). For primary CTAs (Compose, Set Up).
- **`responsive`** — Action button on desktop (≥768px), kebab on mobile. For management actions (Edit, Photo, Delete).
- **`kebab`** — Always in dropdown. For safety actions (Flag, Block).

Header action buttons follow **Tier 1 (rounded rectangle)** from the shape hierarchy in `lwc-css-foundations`. They must never use pill shape (`9999px`).

Item shape: `{ key, label, icon, display, variant }`. `icon` = filename from `Impact_Icons` (e.g., `'edit.png'`). `variant`: `'primary'` (teal fill) or `'danger'` (red tint on hover). Kebab trigger only appears when items would render inside it.

```javascript
get headerMenuItems() {
    if (this.isPosterPersona) {
        return [
            { key: 'edit', label: 'Edit', icon: 'edit.png', display: 'responsive' },
            { key: 'photo', label: 'Photo', icon: 'photo.png', display: 'responsive' },
            { key: 'delete', label: 'Delete', icon: 'trash.png', display: 'responsive', variant: 'danger' }
        ];
    }
    return [{ key: 'flag', label: 'Report', icon: 'warning.png', display: 'kebab' }];
}
handleHeaderMenuAction(event) {
    const actions = { edit: () => this.handleEdit(), photo: () => this.handleUploadPhoto(), delete: () => this.handleDeleteClick(), flag: () => this.handleFlag() };
    actions[event.detail.key]?.();
}
```

**Never** use deprecated `slot="actions"`, `showCustomAction`, or `showMenu`. All actions via `menuItems`. Do not build custom header markup — always use `c-fimby-page-header`.

## Image URL Resolution (Organization ID Suffix)

CMS images require the Salesforce Org ID suffix. Every LWC displaying user-uploaded images must:

1. Import: `import getOrganizationId from '@salesforce/apex/FimbyHomeController.getOrganizationId';`
2. Fetch in `connectedCallback`: `this._organizationId = await getOrganizationId();` (cacheable=true)
3. Process URLs:

```javascript
_completeImageUrl(url) {
    if (!url) return '';
    if (this._organizationId && !url.includes(this._organizationId)) {
        return url + this._organizationId;
    }
    return url;
}
```

Apply to all image URLs from Apex/records. Do **not** apply to static resource URLs (`IMPACT_ICONS`, `MEMES*`, `FIMBY_Brand`).

## Persona-First Detail Pages (Technical)

Detail pages use 3 persona getters: `isPosterPersona`, `isResponderPersona`, `isRespondedPersona`. Client-side only (no new Apex). Single-column layout at all viewports. Poster actions via `headerMenuItems` (`responsive` display), viewer safety via `headerMenuItems` (`kebab` display). Reference: `fimbyNeedOfferDetail`, `fimbyBulkBuyDetailBody`.

## Event Type Config (CONFIG-Driven Getters)

`fimbyNeedOfferDetail` uses an `EVENT_TYPE_CONFIG` object keyed by `Event_Type__c` value (`Gathering`, `Open_Event`, `Community_Event`). All event-specific getters resolve through `this.eventTypeConfig.property` instead of nested if/else. When adding event behavior, **add a property to the config object** — do not introduce ad-hoc conditionals.

Key config flags: `usesCapacity`, `usesQuickResponse`, `usesResponseThreads`, `usesOnDemandEventChat`, `usesAttendeeList`, `showMessagePoster`, `showGuestStepper`, `showModeration`, `showEventLink`.

**Critical**: `usesCapacity` is `true` only for Gathering. Open Event and Community Event must never enter capacity exhaustion paths (`isQuantityExhausted`, "Event Full", disabled CTA). Gate all capacity logic behind `isGathering`.

## Quick-Response Modal (`fimbyQuickResponseModal`)

All response interactions from feeds use `fimbyQuickResponseModal` — a single reusable modal with type-switching variants. **Do not navigate to `/respond`, `/reserve-share`, or `/borrow-item`** — those routes are deprecated.

| Type | From Feed | From Detail |
|---|---|---|
| Community Event | Inline 1-click (no modal) | Inline 1-click |
| Open Event | Modal (guest stepper) | Inline 1-click + post-RSVP stepper |
| Gathering / Ask / Offer | Form modal | Form modal |
| Bulk Buy | Form modal (amount stepper) | Form modal |
| Library | Form modal (date + days) | Form modal |
| Story | Comment modal | Existing `fimbyCommentComposer` |

After modal close or inline action, cards/detail pages update in-place (no page reload, scroll preserved).

## Confetti — DOM-Based Only

Celebrations use `fireEmojiConfetti({ emojis, style, intensity })` from `fimbyConfettiHelper`. This is a pure-DOM engine using `element.animate()` (Web Animations API). **Do not** import `loadScript(CONFETTI)`, `buildEmojiShapes`, or any canvas-based confetti API — the canvas approach is deprecated due to cross-platform emoji rendering failures in WebView. The `Confetti` static resource exists only as rollback insurance.

## Character-Limited Text Fields

Every text input or textarea with a `maxlength` must follow this pattern:

1. **`maxlength` matches the Salesforce field length exactly** — never set a higher value. The counter display and the HTML limit must agree.
2. **Always show a counter** in the `field-label-row`: `<span class={countClass}>{length}/{max}</span>`
3. **Counter colour changes dynamically** via a class getter:

```javascript
get fieldCountClass() {
    const len = this.fieldValue.length;
    if (len >= MAX) return 'character-count at-limit';
    if (len >= Math.floor(MAX * 0.9)) return 'character-count near-limit';
    return 'character-count';
}
```

4. **CSS** (scoped per component — add once if missing):

```css
.character-count.near-limit {
    color: var(--fimby-warning, #C07B2A);
    font-weight: 500;
}
.character-count.at-limit {
    color: var(--fimby-error, #C13030);
    font-weight: 600;
}
```

Some components use `char-count` as the base class instead of `character-count` — match whichever the component already uses, but always include `.near-limit` and `.at-limit` modifiers.

5. **Hard limits, not soft** — `maxlength` enforces the cap; the browser stops input at the limit. Do not allow overage and block submit. The counter turns red *at* the limit (`>=`), not above it (`>`).
6. **Prefer native `<input>` / `<textarea>`** over `lightning-input` / `lightning-textarea` in modals and compact forms. Lightning base components reserve internal padding for help text and error slots even when unused, causing layout bloat. Native elements give full CSS control.

## Collapsible Sections

Tracked boolean + chevron `<button>` + `slideDown` CSS. Mobile default: collapsed. Desktop: expanded (via `window.matchMedia('(min-width: 768px)')` in `connectedCallback`). Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`. Inline per consumer — no shared component. Used in `fimbyRecordDetailCard` and `fimbyNeedOfferDetail`.

## Loading Choreography (smooth transitions, no chunky reveals)

FIMBY hides intermediate loading states and reveals each surface **fully formed, once**, with a gentle fade. Never let a page render an empty frame, then a spinner, then content popping in piece by piece. Four codified patterns:

### 1. Hide-until-loaded reveal (detail pages)

Gate the **entire** content body behind a single readiness flag; show only the spinner until **every** critical, layout-defining load resolves, then render and fade in once.

```javascript
@track _detailReady = false;
_recordDone = false; _secondaryDone = false;

get showLoadingState() { return this.showRemovedState ? false : !this._detailReady; }
get showContent()      { return this._detailReady && this.shouldRenderRecord; }

_maybeMarkReady() {                       // call from every load's completion (success AND error)
    if (this.isRemoved) { this._detailReady = true; return; }
    if (!this._recordDone) return;
    if (!this.record) { this._detailReady = true; return; }   // error → reveal the error state
    if (!this._secondaryDone) return;     // wait for responses/comments/admin/etc.
    this._detailReady = true;
}
```

```css
.detail-content { animation: detailFadeIn 220ms ease; }
@keyframes detailFadeIn { from { opacity: 0; } to { opacity: 1; } }
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .detail-content { animation: none; } }
```

Reference: `fimbyNeedOfferDetail`, `fimbyStoryDetail`, `fimbyLibraryItemDetail`, `fimbySkillOfferDetail`. Don't reveal sections incrementally; don't gate on non-layout/optional fetches.

### 2. Feed curtain (lists)

Use `fimbyInfiniteScroll` for all feeds (Home, Notifications, Messages, Library) — **don't roll your own list shell.** It lays content out at `opacity: 0` behind a curtain and reveals in a single fade once the first page renders, with a ~350ms minimum to avoid a flash and a reserved `--fimby-feed-curtain-min-height` so the page doesn't jump. Pass `initial-loading-label` for the curtain copy.

### 3. Image fade-in

User-uploaded images start `opacity: 0` and transition to `1` on `load`; a `renderedCallback` sweep marks already-`complete` (cached) images loaded immediately so they don't flash. Reduced-motion shows instantly. Reference: `fimbyImageGrid` (`handleImageLoad` + `.is-loaded`). Apply the same to thumbnails rendered outside the grid.

### 4. Silent scroll restore (cache resume)

When restoring a cached feed + scroll position on back-navigation, hold the list invisible from first paint, `window.scrollTo` while hidden (nested `requestAnimationFrame`), then fade in at the restored position so the scroll jump is never visible. Reduced-motion instant. Reference: `fimbyHomeFeed`, `fimbyLibraryBrowser` (`_resumeHidden` + `scrollContainerClass`). Pairs with the soft-nav back-restore (flush cached scroll state in `disconnectedCallback`, since `pagehide` doesn't fire on soft nav).

## Onboarding Structure

- **Signup** (pre-account): `FIMBY_Public_Signup_Page` flow at `/sign-up`; standard Experience Cloud self-register at `/register`. No LWC — not `fimbyUserRegistration` (removed; was never wired live).
- **Profile setup** (`fimbyOnboardingPage` at `/onboarding`): post-login Phase 1 — name required; photo, about-you, care prefs, vouch optional. Replaces legacy `fimbyOnboardingModal`.
- **Walkthrough**: Phase 2 of `fimbyOnboardingPage` (hard-coded content in `fimbyWalkthroughContent.js`); dismissible per-session or permanently via Apex flags.

## User Feedback — Toasts & Inline Banners (NO ShowToastEvent)

`ShowToastEvent` / `lightning/platformShowToastEvent` does **not** render in our LWR Experience Cloud site — it silently no-ops. Never import or dispatch it. Two mechanisms, each one job:

- **Operation failure** (server/FLS/network): `fireToast` / `fireErrorToast` from `c/fimbyToastHelper` → shell-mounted `c-fimby-toast` (global, assertive, auto-dismiss). Mounted once in `fimbyUniversalHeader` — don't add per page. Variants: `error` (default) / `warning` / `info` (no `success`).
- **In-form validation** ("Name is required"): `c-fimby-inline-banner variant="error"` next to the field — never a toast.
- **Success**: `c-fimby-inline-banner variant="success"` only if the user stays on the surface; **nothing** if the action navigates away or removes the item from a list (the surface change is the confirmation).

`c-fimby-inline-banner` handles `role`/`aria-live` (error/warning = alert/assertive, success/info = status/polite), renders nothing when `message` is empty, icon + text always. Don't hand-roll `errorMessage`/`_error`/`this.error` banner markup — route through it. Reference: `fimbyModeratorTaskPage` + `fimbyModeratorDashboard`.
